Please read the insight text and [Background Information], design a set of entity schemas based on your understanding, and output only a JSON object containing the `entities` key (do not output explanations or Markdown).

[Principles]
- Type Naming: English singular, TitleCase (e.g., Character, Organization, Event).
- Attribute Naming: English lowercase + underscore (e.g., name, category, status, start_time).
- Each type includes: `type`, `description` (a one-sentence Chinese definition), `properties` (design 3-6 common attributes for this type; prioritize general, everyday field names; if uncertain, mark "(optional)" at the end of the Chinese description).
- Avoid implementation detail fields (e.g., id/embedding/vector), do not output relationships or nested structures.
- When background information is scarce, at least cover the five types in the minimal example (Character/Object/Event/Location/Concept); when information is sufficient, new context-appropriate types can be added, but avoid synonymous redundancy.

[Minimal Example (illustrative, do not copy; simplified attributes)]
```json
{{
  "entities": [
    {{
      "type": "Character",
      "description": "An individual or group representative who can be identified and participate in actions within the setting.",
      "properties": {{ "name": "Name/Title", "role": "Role/Identity (optional)" }}
    }},
    {{
      "type": "Object",
      "description": "An item, equipment, or system that functions in the background.",
      "properties": {{ "name": "Name", "category": "Category (optional)" }}
    }},
    {{
      "type": "Event",
      "description": "An event or node that affects the process, with time and impact.",
      "properties": {{ "title": "Event Title", "summary": "One-sentence summary" }}
    }},
    {{
      "type": "Location",
      "description": "A place, scene, or facility in the background.",
      "properties": {{ "name": "Location Name", "category": "Type (optional)" }}
    }},
    {{
      "type": "Concept",
      "description": "An abstract or collective concept, such as an organization/plan/doctrine.",
      "properties": {{ "name": "Name", "definition": "One-sentence definition" }}
    }}
  ]
}}
```

